name: Jamie Larkin
text: They do not refrigerate after making, so you will pick up a floppy mess. The thin crust is so thin it is difficult to move to another pan (or even remove from the cardboard it comes on). Pretty much just brought home to through away. Very frustrating.

name: Christopher Gallati
text: Online ordering is a waste of time! I have ordered with more than 30min time and confirmation states should be ready in plenty of time, yet I consistently have to wait for pizzas to be made. Maybe get an app and staff stores for peak â€¦More

name: Lori Johnson
text: Great pizza made to order, ready to bake when I'm ready to eat. The prices are affordable and Ebt is also accepted.

name: Holly Maiden
text: Clean, fast, friendly service with the best quality pizza for Great price!!

name: Asset Realty
text: Absolutely terrible.  There was a used bandaid baked into the pizza and I chewed on it.  So gross and sickening.  I'll never go back.  Karen Surace

name: Andrew Bush
text: Shift Leader Teri deserves a raise. Not only did she make a great pizza, I saw her handle an entitled housewife like a champ. The lady was being extremely rude and demanding for no reason and Teri kept her calm and never once cracked. Management should consider promoting her ASAP

name: Robert Trentham
text: Cant get enough of this place.

name: Patty Magnee
text: Great pizza, especially the Chicago Stuffed

name: A Smith
text: Was told would be ready in 20-30 minutes and it took over 1 hour. Very long waits.

name: Deena Greer
text: need more staff. It was a one woman show tonight with taking our order, making the pizza, etc. we also got 2 salads. The lettuce was not washed and dirt was in the lettuce leaves.
